headline: LG Electronics Expects Quarterly Profit to Halve Amid Higher Logistics Costs
summary: The South Korean consumer-electronics giant forecast a 53% drop in fourth-quarter operating profit, as its television and auto-component businesses remained sluggish.

headline: Samsung Expects Further Profit Growth Slowdown, Missing Estimates
summary: The world’s largest maker of memory chips and smartphones said sluggish demand for conventional chips used in personal computers and mobile phones weighed on its memory business for the quarter.
